               <history>
                  <origin notBefore="1300" notAfter="1399">Written in <origPlace>Norway</origPlace>.
                     Accoring to <bibl><ref target="ONPindices">ONP</ref></bibl> the manuscript can
                     be dated to <origDate notBefore="1300" notAfter="1399">s. XIV in, s. XIV ex and
                        s. XIV med</origDate>. <list>
                        <item>Fols 1r-11v og 13r-64v: The beginning of the fourteenth century (<bibl>
                              <ref type="secondary-1" target="KKKat">Katalog</ref>
                              <biblScope unit="volume">I</biblScope>
                              <biblScope unit="page">383</biblScope>
                           </bibl> and <bibl>
                              <ref type="secondary-1" target="NgL4">Storm 1885</ref>
                              <biblScope unit="page">562</biblScope>
                           </bibl>).</item>
                           <item>Fol. 12 was inserted later and dates from the end of the
                           fourteenth century (<bibl>
                              <ref type="secondary-1" target="KKKat">Katalog</ref>
                              <biblScope unit="volume">I</biblScope>
                              <biblScope unit="page">384</biblScope>
                           </bibl> and <bibl>
                              <ref type="secondary-1" target="NgL4">Storm 1885</ref>,
                           ibid.</bibl>).</item>
                        <item>Fols 65-66: c. 1350 (<bibl>
                              <ref type="secondary-1" target="NgL4">Storm 1885</ref>, ibid. </bibl>
                           and <bibl>
                              <ref target="Seip1955">Seip 1955</ref>
                              <biblScope unit="page">229</biblScope>
                           </bibl>). <name type="person" key="KriKaa001">Kålund</name>'s (<bibl>
                              <ref type="secondary-1" target="KKKat">Katalog</ref>
                           </bibl>) dating of this part is uncertain as he calls it "en noget yngre
                           hånd end det foregående". ("a somewhat younger hand than the previous"
                           e.g. fols 1r-11v and 13r-64v).</item>
                     </list>
